│ THOUGHT: Good. Now we have changed the condition to freeze whenever there is any bool logic op, regardless of sizes. This should add a freeze in the bug case, which may fix the miscompilation? However,      │
│ freezing the vectorized root may still not be enough because the vector reduction intrinsic will still see a frozen poison element (which becomes an arbitrary value). If the arbitrary value is false, and    │
│ another element is true, the result is true, which matches the expected result. If the arbitrary value is true, also true. So the result is correct as long as there is another true element. In the bug,      │
│ there are true elements, so the result should be true. However, the vector reduction intrinsic will produce poison if any element is poison, but after freezing, there is no poison. So the result will be     │
│ true. That should fix the bug.                                                                                                                                                                                 │
